	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />About music he probably means the available FamiTracker and other options that could be used in a homebrew project to allow many composers familiar with FamiTracker to work with you. The original NES developers didn't have such a music/sound engine available to them. They had to make it. Similarly there are graphical editors we have that they didn't. And in general computers are better, and we have emulators with debuggers.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


